The paper deals with the application of deep neural networks for vehicle control, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The use of artificial neural networks for control also suggests the possibility of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of Multi-Layer Perceptron (MLP) and Convolutional Neural Network (CNN), which are common architectures used in deep learning and machine learning, respectively, indicating the relevance of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with the evaluation of the performance of the models based on their ability to drive the vehicle on a challenging test track, which suggests the relevance of robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper mentions the use of simulations, which suggests the relevance of computer vision (cs.CV) in generating the dataset.
